\N<Onee-chan>Huh? What are you doing in a place like this?
The buses don't come until evening, you know? The buses here
only come twice a day.
\N<Boku>I'm waiting for the old lady here.
\N<Onee-chan>Old lady? Um... what's your name?
\N<Boku>I'm 'Boku'! Everyone calls me 'Boku'.

\N<Onee-chan>I see. I'm Harumi. Nice to meet you, Boku-kun.
So, is this 'old lady' you're waiting for a relative of
yours, Boku-kun?

\N<Boku>Yeah, that's right. She's my dad's younger sister.
My mom is busy because she's going to have a baby, so during
summer vacation, I'm going to live at this old lady's house.
That's why my dad and I came here by bus.

\N<Boku>But, my dad is so absent-minded, he told me to get
off and it turns out it's one bus stop earlier.

\N<Boku>I tried to just get back on the bus and go home, but
I realized I had gone all the way to the next bus stop.
Geez, I messed up.

\N<Boku>When we arrived at the foot of the mountain, he told
me to call the old lady and have her come pick me up, so I'm
waiting here.
\N<Onee-chan>Hehe. That must have been tough for you.
